      "date": "2021-06-14 21:09:26.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nHave you guys looked at whether this sort of infrastructure, if it were available for all LNDs, would be sufficient to determine local NI health? i.e. could we get rid of the recovery pings for local NIs and replace it completely with these link events?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "6f03c1910f8ea12c1804bc98fa62df04a49677fd",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 824,
        "name": "Serguei Smirnov",
        "email": "ssmirnov@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "ssmirnov"
      },
      "date": "2021-06-16 00:17:00.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> Have you guys looked at whether this sort of infrastructure, if it\n > were available for all LNDs, would be sufficient to determine local\n > NI health? i.e. could we get rid of the recovery pings for local\n > NIs and replace it completely with these link events?\n\nI agree that would be cleaner. The problem is that with socklnd, for example, it is possible that the link comes back up with no IP assigned to it anymore: it that case trying to ping still makes sense. So these IP-level events would be separate from link-level events. I'm guessing it would be possible to subscribe for these too somehow, I just haven't explored it in enough detail.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
